					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2893766&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204188" alt="Croquembouche" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2893766)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;" >Croquembouche</a></span> <span class="odate time_1528127122 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Jun 2018 15:45</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3824232">
									

<p>I saw this in your sandbox a few times so maybe I've had a little longer to dwell on my thoughts</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Criticism</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I agree with a lot of the stuff that OptimisticLucio said.</p>
<p>The SCP itself feels very bland, just a superpowered dude who managed to convince the O5s to release him and all his power. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Feels like Dr Manhattan with the manipulation reversed.</span> It has been pointed out to me that Manhattan wore a watch</p>
<p>Desmet and O5-1 also feel like just avatars for advancing the plot (I forget the technical term), they lack any personality of their own. As a result, I believe the dialogue could use some refining, as it seems far too basic and/or &quot;intentionally mysterious&quot;:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-001: I can see everything.<br />
O5-1: Do you know what you're looking for?<br />
SCP-001: The mirror.<br />
O5-1: Do it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The clinical tone is&#8230; odd, in places. I don't want to say &quot;off&quot;, but it's not quite spot on, either. The section beginning &quot;<em>O5-1 collapses in on himself, folding and distorting down into a single point</em>&quot; is a good example of this. Who's writing? Whose perspective is this segment from? How does this portion of the text exist? The writing quality here is excellent, but it's from the viewpoint of an omniscient narrator and that breaks the immersion for me.</p>
<p><em>EDIT: Read your response to Lucio about this being written by Overseers for Overseers, and I guess I can excuse it in that case. Either way, even if it's O5-3 writing this stuff, he's being awfully descriptive about it.</em></p>
<p>Plotwise things don't really make sense, but Lucio covered that in far less words than I would. I also feel like everything that's here is on the surface, I don't need to do any digging to find out backstory - I could well be wrong, but if I'm not, that's not always a bad thing honestly.</p>
<p>While I respect completely that this is part of a contest, I'm of the opinion that a 001 should be a self-contained work in and of itself, and to have this unfinished feeling lingering over it taints it for me, sort of reduces the value of having an 001 itself. Maybe I'm a bit of a traditionalist when it comes to that :P</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Praise</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Formatting is excellent - especially the addenda titles, and even the spacing on the content boxes.</p>
<p>I really, really love the photo of DEEPWELL #9. That sort of architecture really gets my motors going.</p>
<p>As usual, the writing quality is stellar throughout. I've written paragraphs in the previous spoiler and only a few lines for this one, but when I say stellar I really mean it. It counts for a lot.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Overall, it's a no-vote from me. Perhaps extra context from future entries in the contest series will swing me one way or the other.</p>
<p>EDIT: After a couple of days, the absolute implication that this <em>is</em> 001, branding the other proposals as decoys (no matter how true that is); and the fact that I feel I shouldn't be underwhelmed by a 001 has led to my downvote. Again, perhaps future contest entries will sway that vote.</p>

